column18: 09/03/2015: Assailants set fire to an asylum seekers' center in Vao village, Laane-Viru county, Estonia. No one was injured, but the center was slightly damaged in the blaze. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
column64: The specific motive is unknown; however, sources suspected that the attack was related to Estonia's resettlement policy of refugees.
column108: An asylum center building was damaged in this attack.

column18: 12/18/2015: An explosives-laden vehicle detonated in a parking lot in Tallinn, Harju, Estonia. There were no reported casualties resulting from the blast. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
